The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 December is 10,619 (1,229.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 09 December, there were 744 new confirmed cases (86.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 December, there were 498 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 49% (246 extra cases).
